The paper deals with the problem of learning Markov Random Fields (MRFs) under the constraint of differential privacy. This involves both structure learning and parameter learning. The paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with learning MRFs. It also involves privacy constraints, which could lead to categorization under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves algorithms and lower bounds, which could lead to categorization under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
